---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — CryptoBonusWorld"
  description="Privacy Policy for CryptoBonusWorld.com. How we collect, use and protect your data."
  canonical="/privacy-policy/"
  noindex
>
  <div class="container">
    <Breadcrumbs crumbs={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'Privacy Policy' },
    ]} />
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>CryptoBonusWorld.com is a static informational website. We do not require registration or collect personal information directly. The following data may be collected through third-party tools:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Analytics</strong> — We may use analytics tools (such as Google Analytics or Cloudflare Web Analytics) that collect aggregated, anonymized data about page views, referral sources, and browser information.</li>
        <li><strong>Affiliate Click Tracking</strong> — When you click affiliate links, the destination exchange may use cookies and tracking pixels to attribute your registration. This is controlled by the exchange's own privacy policy.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>Our website may use cookies for analytics purposes only. We do not use cookies for advertising profiling. You can disable cookies in your browser settings.</p>

      <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>This website contains links to third-party exchanges and services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those third parties. Review the privacy policy of each exchange before registering.</p>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We do not store personal data on our servers. Analytics data is retained according to the third-party provider's policies.</p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to access, correct or delete data held about you. Contact us if you have privacy-related requests.</p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Continued use of the website after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>For privacy-related questions, please use our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.</p>

      <p><em>Last updated: May 2026</em></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
